Key Findings
- The Central Difference O(h²) method provides highly accurate numerical approximations.
- A smaller step size (*h*) significantly reduces the relative error.
- The approximation error decreased from **0.132%** to **0.0013%** when using a finer interval.
- Microsoft Excel can effectively perform numerical differentiation and error analysis without requiring programming languages.

